{{for|the Michigan Tech building|Advanced Technology Development Complex}}
The '''Advanced Technology Development Center''' (ATDC) is a science and [[business incubator]] in [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]. It is part of the [[Enterprise Innovation Institute]] (EI2) at the [[Georgia Institute of Technology]], and is headquartered in [[Technology Square]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catalog.gatech.edu/supportfac/atdc.php|title=Advanced Technology Development Center|publisher=Georgia Tech Research Support Facilities|accessdate=2007-08-08| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070817191102/http://www.catalog.gatech.edu/supportfac/atdc.php| archivedate= 17 August 2007 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref> ATDC was formed in 1980 to stimulate growth in Georgia's technology business base, and admitted its first member company in 1981.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atdc.org/history.asp |title=History |publisher=Advanced Technology Development Center |accessdate=2007-08-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070607203832/http://www.atdc.org/history.asp |archivedate=2007-06-07 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> It now has locations in [[Atlanta, Georgia|Atlanta]] and [[Savannah, Georgia|Savannah]]. In 2011, ATDC expanded its mission by merging with Georgia Tech’s [[VentureLab]] and with the Georgia SBIR Assistance Program. ATDC has opened its membership to all technology entrepreneurs in Georgia, from those at the earliest conception stage to the well-established, venture-fundable companies.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://atdc.org/about/about|title=About ATDC|publisher=Advanced Technology Development Center|accessdate=2011-10-12}}</ref>

More than 120 companies started there, including firms such as [[MindSpring]] (now part of [[EarthLink]]) and [[TransNexus]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atdc.org/graduates.asp |title=Graduates |publisher=Advanced Technology Development Center |accessdate=2007-08-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070626091719/http://www.atdc.org/graduates.asp |archivedate=2007-06-26 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> Sponsored companies have created almost 51,000 man-years of employment, generated over $12.7 billion revenue, generated over $100 million in profit to Georgia, and raised over $1 billion in [[venture capital]] since 1999.<ref name="suc">{{cite web|url=http://atdc.org/success.asp |title=Success |publisher=Advanced Technology Development Center |accessdate=2007-08-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070608112119/http://www.atdc.org/success.asp |archivedate=2007-06-08 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> ATDC has been recognized by [[Inc. (magazine)|Inc. Magazine]] and [[BusinessWeek|Business Week]] as one of the nation's top incubators, and won several other awards.<ref name="suc"/><ref>{{cite news|first=Rifka|last=Rosenwein|url=http://www.inc.com/magazine/20001101/20906.html|title=The Idea Factories|work=Inc. Magazine|date=2000-11-01|accessdate=2007-08-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite pressrelease|url=http://www.gatech.edu/newsroom/release.html?id=378 |title=Georgia Tech’s Advanced Technology Development Center Wins Award for Technology-led Economic Development Efforts |publisher=Georgia Institute of Technology |date=2004-06-10 |accessdate=2007-08-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090222034126/http://www.gatech.edu/newsroom/release.html?id=378 |archivedate=February 22, 2009 }}</ref>

