{{For|the book series published by Continuum|History of Technology (book series)}} {{Infobox journal | title = History and Technology | cover = History and Technology (journal).jpg | editor = Martin Collins | discipline = [[History of technology]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Hist. Technol. | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/ghat | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 185681834 | LCCN = 88656216 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0734-1512 | eISSN = 1477-2620 }} '''''History and Technology''''' is a quarterly [[peer review]]ed [[academic journal]] devoted to publishing papers on all aspects of the [[history of technology]]. It was established in 1983. One of the founding editors was [[Pietro Redondi]]. The subjects range from ancient and classical times to the present day. The current publisher is [[Taylor & Francis]].
